Students of ABRHS can get a FREE and LEGAL copy of Microsoft Office through the Office for Education program. The program includes the following:
<ul>
	<li>5 Installs of Microsoft Office 365 Education Plus, which includes:
<ul>
	<li>Office 2013 editions of Word, PowerPoint, Excel, OneNote, Access, Publisher, Outlook, and InfoPath</li>
	<li>Skype for Business, OneDrive for Business</li>
</ul>
</li>
	<li>Office Online, which includes:
<ul>
	<li>Online editions of Word, OneNote, PowerPoint, and Excel</li>
	<li>OneDrive, Sites, Delve, Video, and Sway</li>
</ul>
</li>
	<li>Free Updates to Office 2016 apps in February 2016</li>
</ul>
To get your free copy of Office, follow the following steps:
<ol>
	<li>Go to the following website: <a href="https://products.office.com/en-us/student/office-in-education?tab=students">https://products.office.com/en-us/student/office-in-education?tab=students</a></li>
	<li>In the box labeled ‚ÄúEnter your school email address‚Äù, enter your school username followed by ‚Äú@mail.ab.mec.edu.‚Äù For example, if my username is 17doej, I would enter ‚Äú17doej@mail.ab.mec.edu‚Äù</li>
	<li>Click ‚ÄúI‚Äôm a student‚Äù</li>
	<li>Check your school email. The subject should be ‚ÄúFinish signing up for Office 365 Education‚Äù. It might take a couple minutes to show up, so be patient.</li>
	<li>Click the button labeled ‚ÄúYes, that‚Äôs me.‚Äù</li>
	<li>This will open a website with a signup form. Fill it out.</li>
	<li>After filling out the form, you will be taken to the Office portal home page. Here, you can access Office Online apps, and install a copy of Office 2013. You can return to this page at anytime by going to <a href="https://portal.office.com/">https://portal.office.com/</a>, and signing in with the email address you used in step 2.</li>
	<li>Enjoy!</li>
</ol>
